<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1284&amp;p=11703#p11703"><![CDATA[
I would also like to know how these 2600 cart cases were produced. I suppose Ronen at videogame wiz should know, since they're selling them.<br /><br />Otherwise, I agree with Kevin. Making grand plans about mass-production of new NES carts is just silly when we have yet to see a homebrewn NES game of good enough quality that more than 100 carts could be sold. And the few nostalgics that won't settle for playing a new homebrewn game in an emulator probably won't mind spending $50 or more on it anyway.<br /><br />I too would really like to see the lockout chip get 0wn3d, but no one in their right mind should believe that the lockout chip is what's keeping people from making NES games today. The real reason is that there aren't many people in this world that will devote the time needed to make a big NES game just for the fun of it. Most big homebrewn-game projects get terminated before they reach halfway. The ones that do get finished are smaller games, where the author had more realistic goals for his hobby project.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=106">Bananmos</a> — Sat Apr 08, 2006 11:27 am</p><hr />
