Also remember that Atari carts are tiny compared to NES ones, the cart shell and the board.  And they only need one memory chip (and a logic chip).  Compared to NES NROM carts that need 2 memories and some illogic (lockout <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> ).<br /><br />Which doesn't make the prototyping cheaper, but does make it easier to make a bunch of them at once.  NES ones will just cost a little more (which is a little multiplied by some crazy quantity for the builder, it becomes a lot).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Apr 07, 2006 7:14 am</p><hr />
